Content:
'''Kiev Pecherski [[Monastery]]''', also known as  '''Kiev Cave Monastery''', '''Kievo-Pecherskaya Lavra''', '''Kiev Pecherska Lavra''', is an ancient underground, [[cave monastery]] in the vicinity of [[Kiev]]. It was founded in [[1051]] by monks Antoni and Feodosi and has become an important center of [[Orthodox]] [[Christianity]] in [[Kievan Rus']].

The word ''pechera'' is ''cave'' in [[Ukrainian language]]. The word ''lavra'' is used for monasteries of high rank in [[Eastern Orthodox Church]].

