 The Kyiv Pechersk Lavra contains numerous architectural monuments, ranging from [[bell tower]]s to cathedrals to cave systems and to strong stone [[Lavra fortification|fortification walls]]. The main attractions of the Lavra include the [[Great Lavra Belltower]], and the [[Cathedral of the Dormition (Pechersk Lavra)|Dormition Cathedral]], destroyed in [[World War II]] by Soviet forces, and fully reconstructed in recent years.{{when|date=September 2018}} 

 Other churches and cathedrals of the Lavra include: the [[Refectory Church (Pechersk Lavra)|Refectory Church]], the Church of All Saints, the [[Church of the Saviour at Berestove]], the Church of the Exaltation of Cross, the Church of the Trinity, the Church of the Nativity of the Virgin, the Church of the Conception of St. Anne, and the Church of the Life-Giving Spring. The Lavra also contains many other constructions, including: the St. Nicholas Monastery, the Kyiv Theological Academy and Seminary, and the Debosquette Wall.{{cn|date=January 2023}}

